ausMibStatusRevMajor.name: ausMibStatusRevMajor
ausMibStatusRevMajor.description: The major number of the revision of the Adaptec Universal Storage MIB.

ausMibStatusRevMinor.name: ausMibStatusRevMinor
ausMibStatusRevMinor.description: The minor number of the revision of the Adaptec Universal Storage MIB.

ausMibStatusSecondsSinceInitiation.name: ausMibStatusSecondsSinceInitiation
ausMibStatusSecondsSinceInitiation.description: The number of elapsed seconds since this SNMP subagent was initiated.

ausMibStatusCopyright.name: ausMibStatusCopyright
ausMibStatusCopyright.description: Copyright notification. This string shall always be reported as 'Copyright (C) 2011 PMC-Sierra, Inc'. The year may be modified as appropriate.

ausMibStatusOverall.name: ausMibStatusOverall
ausMibStatusOverall.description: Overall operational status. This is the 'worst' overall status of all controllers reported in the MIB.

ausAggregatedControllerIndex.name: ausAggregatedControllerIndex
ausAggregatedControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each aggregated controller beginning with 1.

ausAggregatedControllerList.name: ausAggregatedControllerList
ausAggregatedControllerList.description: A list of indices into the ausControllerTable specifying the controllers that are aggregated by a software driver to form an array.

ausControllerIndex.name: ausControllerIndex
ausControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each controller beginning with 1.

ausControllerUniqueId.name: ausControllerUniqueId
ausControllerUniqueId.description: An ID for this controller that is unique across all namespaces.

ausControllerDescription.name: ausControllerDescription
ausControllerDescription.description: Free form text for additional description of the controller.

ausControllerHostBusType.name: ausControllerHostBusType
ausControllerHostBusType.description: Type of host computer system bus for this controller.

ausControllerHostBusMaximumTransferRate.name: ausControllerHostBusMaximumTransferRate
ausControllerHostBusMaximumTransferRate.description: Maximum possible transfer rate on the host bus in megabytes per second.

ausControllerNumberOfChannels.name: ausControllerNumberOfChannels
ausControllerNumberOfChannels.description: The number of channels present on this controller.

ausControllerHighestChannelWithDevices.name: ausControllerHighestChannelWithDevices
ausControllerHighestChannelWithDevices.description: The 0-relative channel number within the controller which has at least one device attached to it.

ausControllerInstalledMemory.name: ausControllerInstalledMemory
ausControllerInstalledMemory.description: Memory installed on this controller in megabytes.

ausControllerAudibleAlarmStatus.name: ausControllerAudibleAlarmStatus
ausControllerAudibleAlarmStatus.description: Status of audible alarm for this controller.

ausControllerBatteryStatus.name: ausControllerBatteryStatus
ausControllerBatteryStatus.description: Status of battery for this controller.

ausControllerZMMStatus.name: ausControllerZMMStatus
ausControllerZMMStatus.description: Status of ZMM for this controller.

ausControllerOverallStatus.name: ausControllerOverallStatus
ausControllerOverallStatus.description: Overall operational status of this controller and its children. This is the 'worst' status of the controller status and that of all arrays and un-arrayed devices attached to this controller.

ausControllerPerformanceMode.name: ausControllerPerformanceMode
ausControllerPerformanceMode.description: To ensure optimal performance of the logical drives in the storage space, the performance mode is used.It improves I/O throughput based on the needs of the application.

ausControllerRelationshipIndex.name: ausControllerRelationshipIndex
ausControllerRelationshipIndex.description: A unique index value for each controller relationship beginning with 1.

ausControllerRelationshipType.name: ausControllerRelationshipType
ausControllerRelationshipType.description: Selects whether this row entry is a relationship between entries in the ausController table or entries in the ausExternalRaidDevice table. Setting of this field determines if the ausControllerRelationshipList is a list of indices in the ausController table or the ausExternalRaidDevice table.

ausControllerRelationshipList.name: ausControllerRelationshipList
ausControllerRelationshipList.description: A list of indices into the appropriate controller table specifying the controllers that are related.

ausControllerRelationshipRelation.name: ausControllerRelationshipRelation
ausControllerRelationshipRelation.description: The attributes of the relationship among the related controllers.

ausI2ORaidControllerTable.name: ausI2ORaidControllerTable
ausI2ORaidControllerTable.description: A list of I2O RAID storage controllers.

ausI2ORaidControllerEntry.name: ausI2ORaidControllerEntry
ausI2ORaidControllerEntry.description: A I2O RAID storage controller entry.

ausI2ORaidControllerIndex.name: ausI2ORaidControllerIndex
ausI2ORaidControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each I2O RAID controller.

ausI2ORaidControllerAddress.name: ausI2ORaidControllerAddress
ausI2ORaidControllerAddress.description: The controller Address (normally displayed in hex.) It is a 32-bit value representing the memory address used by the controller

ausI2ORaidControllerBackgroundTaskPriori.name: ausI2ORaidControllerBackgroundTaskPriority
ausI2ORaidControllerBackgroundTaskPriori.description: This object controls the priority of array background tasks such as Build, Rebuild and Verify for this controller. The values range from 1 to 10. A value of 1 is the slowest but uses the least amount of the controller's bandwidth. While a value of 10 is the fastest but it uses the most bandwidth.

ausI2ORaidControllerMainIndex.name: ausI2ORaidControllerMainIndex
ausI2ORaidControllerMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausControllerTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausI2ORaidControllerTable.

ausCCodeControllerTable.name: ausCCodeControllerTable
ausCCodeControllerTable.description: A list of Container Code storage controllers.

ausCCodeControllerEntry.name: ausCCodeControllerEntry
ausCCodeControllerEntry.description: A Container Code storage controller entry.

ausCCodeControllerIndex.name: ausCCodeControllerIndex
ausCCodeControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each Container Code controller.

ausCCodeControllerPCIBusId.name: ausCCodeControllerPCIBusId
ausCCodeControllerPCIBusId.description: The identifier of the host computer PCI bus the controller is attached to.

ausCCodeControllerPCISlotNumber.name: ausCCodeControllerPCISlotNumber
ausCCodeControllerPCISlotNumber.description: The slot number of the host computer PCI bus the controller is in.

ausCCodeControllerMainIndex.name: ausCCodeControllerMainIndex
ausCCodeControllerMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausControllerTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausCCodeControllerTable.

ausHostRAIDControllerTable.name: ausHostRAIDControllerTable
ausHostRAIDControllerTable.description: A list of HostRAID storage controllers.

ausHostRAIDControllerIndex.name: ausHostRAIDControllerIndex
ausHostRAIDControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each HostRAID controller.

ausHostRAIDControllerPCIBus.name: ausHostRAIDControllerPCIBus
ausHostRAIDControllerPCIBus.description: The PCI bus number of this controller.

ausHostRAIDControllerPCIDevice.name: ausHostRAIDControllerPCIDevice
ausHostRAIDControllerPCIDevice.description: The PCI device number of this controller.

ausHostRAIDControllerPCIFunction.name: ausHostRAIDControllerPCIFunction
ausHostRAIDControllerPCIFunction.description: The PCI function number of this controller.

ausHostRAIDControllerMainIndex.name: ausHostRAIDControllerMainIndex
ausHostRAIDControllerMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausControllerTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausI2ORaidControllerTable.

ausServeRAIDControllerTable.name: ausServeRAIDControllerTable
ausServeRAIDControllerTable.description: A list of ServeRAID storage controllers.

ausServeRAIDControllerIndex.name: ausServeRAIDControllerIndex
ausServeRAIDControllerIndex.description: A unique index value for each ServeRAID controller.

ausServeRAIDControllerBIOSRevision.name: ausServeRAIDControllerBIOSRevision
ausServeRAIDControllerBIOSRevision.description: The B.I.O.S. Revision of this controller.

ausServeRAIDControllerDefaultRebuildRate.name: ausServeRAIDControllerDefaultRebuildRate
ausServeRAIDControllerDefaultRebuildRate.description: The default rebuild rate of this controller.

ausServeRAIDControllerSlotNumber.name: ausServeRAIDControllerSlotNumber
ausServeRAIDControllerSlotNumber.description: The slot number of this controller.

ausServeRAIDControllerMainIndex.name: ausServeRAIDControllerMainIndex
ausServeRAIDControllerMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausControllerTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausServeRAIDControllerTable.

ausChannelIndex.name: ausChannelIndex
ausChannelIndex.description: A unique index value for each channel beginning with 1.

ausChannelLocation.name: ausChannelLocation
ausChannelLocation.description: Indicates whether the channelAusControllerIndex field should be interpreted as an index into the controllerTable or the externalRaidDeviceTable. In other words, shows whether this channel is a channel connected directly to the host or is a back-end channel connected to an external RAID controller.

ausChannelAusControllerIndex.name: ausChannelAusControllerIndex
ausChannelAusControllerIndex.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage controller table containing the entry that hosts this channel, or an index into the externalRaidDevice table containing the external RAID controller that hosts this channel. Where the index points is selected by channelLocation above.

ausChannelAusControllerChannelNumber.name: ausChannelAusControllerChannelNumber
ausChannelAusControllerChannelNumber.description: Channel number within the controller referenced by channelAusControllerIndex. Channels are numbered sequentially starting with 0.

ausChannelType.name: ausChannelType
ausChannelType.description: Physical transmission technology for this channel.

ausChannelTypeDescription.name: ausChannelTypeDescription
ausChannelTypeDescription.description: A finer-grained description for the channel. For example, SCSI may be further refined as 'Ultra160' or 'Ultra320'. IDE may be further refined per the various different performance types available.

ausChannelControllerId.name: ausChannelControllerId
ausChannelControllerId.description: Controller ID number used on this channel. Meaning is dependent on channelType. For example, SCSI channels would report controller SCSI ID in this field. The field is a string to allow for a wide range of addressing schemes.

ausChannelControllerSubId.name: ausChannelControllerSubId
ausChannelControllerSubId.description: Controller SubId number used on this channel. Meaning is dependent on channelType. For example, SCSI channels would report controller SCSI LUN in this field. The field is a string to allow for a wide range of addressing schemes.

ausChannelWidth.name: ausChannelWidth
ausChannelWidth.description: Width of the channel in bits. For example, SCSI would be 8 or 16. Serial interfaces would be 1.

ausChannelMaximumTransferRate.name: ausChannelMaximumTransferRate
ausChannelMaximumTransferRate.description: Maximum transfer rate of this channel in megabytes per second.

ausChannelMaximumAttachments.name: ausChannelMaximumAttachments
ausChannelMaximumAttachments.description: Maximum number of devices that may be attached to this this channel (include controller in the count). In case of SATA, this is the total number of ports. Ports are virtualized into IDs on 'SCSI channels'.

ausChannelOverallStatus.name: ausChannelOverallStatus
ausChannelOverallStatus.description: Overall operational status of this channel. This is the 'worst' status of all arrays and un-arrayed devices attached to this channel.

ausChannelRelationshipIndex.name: ausChannelRelationshipIndex
ausChannelRelationshipIndex.description: A unique index value for each channel relationship beginning with 1.

ausChannelRelationshipList.name: ausChannelRelationshipList
ausChannelRelationshipList.description: A list of indices into the channel table specifying the channels that are related.

ausChannelRelationshipRelation.name: ausChannelRelationshipRelation
ausChannelRelationshipRelation.description: The attributes of the relationship among the related controllers.

ausDeviceIndex.name: ausDeviceIndex
ausDeviceIndex.description: A unique index value for each device beginning with 1.

ausDeviceUniqueId.name: ausDeviceUniqueId
ausDeviceUniqueId.description: An ID for this device that is unique across all namespaces.

ausDeviceAusChannelIndices.name: ausDeviceAusChannelIndices
ausDeviceAusChannelIndices.description: A list of indices into the Adaptec Universal Storage Channel table to which this device is attached. (For detailed information about connections between the device and the channel, refer to the ausDevicePort table.)

ausDeviceTypeGroup.name: ausDeviceTypeGroup
ausDeviceTypeGroup.description: Selects which of the subordinate device tables contains more information about this device.

ausDeviceNumberOfPorts.name: ausDeviceNumberOfPorts
ausDeviceNumberOfPorts.description: Number of entries present in the device port table for this device (which is the same as the number of ports on the device).

ausDeviceLocation.name: ausDeviceLocation
ausDeviceLocation.description: Describes the location of this device in a technology-specific manner. This value usually matches the location string on any traps involving this device.

ausDevicePortIndex.name: ausDevicePortIndex
ausDevicePortIndex.description: A unique index value for each device port beginning with 1.

ausDevicePortUniqueId.name: ausDevicePortUniqueId
ausDevicePortUniqueId.description: An ID for this device port that is unique across all namespaces.

ausDevicePortAusDeviceIndex.name: ausDevicePortAusDeviceIndex
ausDevicePortAusDeviceIndex.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage Device table locating the device that contains this port.

ausDevicePortAusDevicePortNumber.name: ausDevicePortAusDevicePortNumber
ausDevicePortAusDevicePortNumber.description: Port number within the device referenced by ausDevicePortAusDeviceIndex. Ports are numbered sequentially starting with 0.

ausDevicePortAusChannelIndex.name: ausDevicePortAusChannelIndex
ausDevicePortAusChannelIndex.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage Channel table locating the channel to which this device port is attached.

ausDevicePortId.name: ausDevicePortId
ausDevicePortId.description: Port ID number used by this device. Meaning is dependent on channel type. For example, SCSI channels would report device SCSI ID in this field. The field is a string to allow for a wide range of addressing schemes. For non-parallel SCSI this is the virtual SCSI targetId

ausDevicePortSubId.name: ausDevicePortSubId
ausDevicePortSubId.description: Port SubId number used by this device. Meaning is dependent on channel type. For example, SCSI channels would report device SCSI LUN in this field. The field is a string to allow for a wide range of addressing schemes. For non-parallel SCSI this is the virtual SCSI LUN

ausDevicePortWidth.name: ausDevicePortWidth
ausDevicePortWidth.description: Port width capability of this device. This may be narrower than the channel width - for example, an eight bit SCSI device on a sixteen bit SCSI channel.

ausDevicePortMaximumTransferRate.name: ausDevicePortMaximumTransferRate
ausDevicePortMaximumTransferRate.description: Maximum transfer rate of this device in megabytes per second.

ausDevicePortNegotiatedTransferRate.name: ausDevicePortNegotiatedTransferRate
ausDevicePortNegotiatedTransferRate.description: Negotiated transfer rate of this device port/ controller channel pair in megabytes per second.

ausDevicePortStatus.name: ausDevicePortStatus
ausDevicePortStatus.description: Operational status of this device port.

ausStorageDeviceIndex.name: ausStorageDeviceIndex
ausStorageDeviceIndex.description: A unique index value for each storage device.

ausStorageDeviceDescription.name: ausStorageDeviceDescription
ausStorageDeviceDescription.description: Free form text for additional description of the storage device.

ausStorageDeviceFormattedCapacity.name: ausStorageDeviceFormattedCapacity
ausStorageDeviceFormattedCapacity.description: Formatted capacity of this storage device in megabytes.

ausStorageDeviceBlockSize.name: ausStorageDeviceBlockSize
ausStorageDeviceBlockSize.description: Physical block size of this storage device in bytes.

ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksLow.name: ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksLow
ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksLow.description: Number of physical blocks for this storage device (least significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksHigh.name: ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksHigh
ausStorageDeviceNumberOfBlocksHigh.description: Number of physical blocks for this storage device (most significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausStorageDeviceRemovableMedia.name: ausStorageDeviceRemovableMedia
ausStorageDeviceRemovableMedia.description: Status of removable media for this storage device.

ausStorageDeviceSmartStatus.name: ausStorageDeviceSmartStatus
ausStorageDeviceSmartStatus.description: S.M.A.R.T. status of this storage device.

ausStorageDeviceMainIndex.name: ausStorageDeviceMainIndex
ausStorageDeviceMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausDeviceTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausStorageDeviceTable.

ausEnclosureDeviceIndex.name: ausEnclosureDeviceIndex
ausEnclosureDeviceIndex.description: A unique index value for each enclosure device.

ausEnclosureDeviceDescription.name: ausEnclosureDeviceDescription
ausEnclosureDeviceDescription.description: Free form text for additional description of the enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfFans.name: ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfFans
ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfFans.description: Number of fans installed in this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfPowerSupplies.name: ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfPowerSupplies
ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfPowerSupplies.description: Number of power supplies installed in this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfSlots.name: ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfSlots
ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfSlots.description: Number of slots installed in this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfTemperatureSen.name: ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfTemperatureSensors
ausEnclosureDeviceNumberOfTemperatureSen.description: Number of temperature sensors installed in this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceIdLow.name: ausEnclosureDeviceIdLow
ausEnclosureDeviceIdLow.description: Unique enclosure ID obtained from inquiry (least significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausEnclosureDeviceIdHigh.name: ausEnclosureDeviceIdHigh
ausEnclosureDeviceIdHigh.description: Unique enclosure ID obtained from inquiry (most significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausEnclosureDeviceStandardRevision.name: ausEnclosureDeviceStandardRevision
ausEnclosureDeviceStandardRevision.description: Revision of standard adhered to for this enclosure (obtained from inquiry).

ausEnclosureDevicePowerOnTime.name: ausEnclosureDevicePowerOnTime
ausEnclosureDevicePowerOnTime.description: Total number of power on minutes for this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDevicePowerCycles.name: ausEnclosureDevicePowerCycles
ausEnclosureDevicePowerCycles.description: Total number of power cycles for this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceDoorLock.name: ausEnclosureDeviceDoorLock
ausEnclosureDeviceDoorLock.description: Presence and current status of this enclosure's door lock.

ausEnclosureDeviceSpeaker.name: ausEnclosureDeviceSpeaker
ausEnclosureDeviceSpeaker.description: Presence and current status of this enclosure's speaker.

ausEnclosureDeviceTemperatureState.name: ausEnclosureDeviceTemperatureState
ausEnclosureDeviceTemperatureState.description: Indicates state of internal temperature for this enclosure.

ausEnclosureDeviceMainIndex.name: ausEnclosureDeviceMainIndex
ausEnclosureDeviceMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausDeviceTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausEnclosureDeviceTable.

ausExternalRaidDeviceTable.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceTable
ausExternalRaidDeviceTable.description: A list of external RAID controllers.

ausExternalRaidDeviceIndex.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceIndex
ausExternalRaidDeviceIndex.description: A unique index value for each external RAID device.

ausExternalRaidDeviceDescription.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceDescription
ausExternalRaidDeviceDescription.description: Free form text for additional description of the external RAID controller.

ausExternalRaidDeviceNumberOfChannels.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceNumberOfChannels
ausExternalRaidDeviceNumberOfChannels.description: The number of back-end channels present on this external RAID controller.

ausExternalRaidDeviceInstalledMemory.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceInstalledMemory
ausExternalRaidDeviceInstalledMemory.description: Installed memory in this external RAID controller in megabytes.

ausExternalRaidDeviceAudibleAlarmStatus.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceAudibleAlarmStatus
ausExternalRaidDeviceAudibleAlarmStatus.description: Status of audible alarm for this external RAID controller.

ausExternalRaidDeviceBatteryStatus.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceBatteryStatus
ausExternalRaidDeviceBatteryStatus.description: Status of battery for this external RAID controller.

ausExternalRaidDeviceMainIndex.name: ausExternalRaidDeviceMainIndex
ausExternalRaidDeviceMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausDeviceTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausExternalRaidDeviceTable.

ausOtherDeviceIndex.name: ausOtherDeviceIndex
ausOtherDeviceIndex.description: A unique index value for each other device.

ausOtherDeviceDescription.name: ausOtherDeviceDescription
ausOtherDeviceDescription.description: Free form text for additional description of this device.

ausOtherDeviceMainIndex.name: ausOtherDeviceMainIndex
ausOtherDeviceMainIndex.description: This is the index into ausDeviceTable of the row that is extended by this row of ausOtherDeviceTable.

ausEnclosureFanIndex.name: ausEnclosureFanIndex
ausEnclosureFanIndex.description: A unique index value for each fan.

ausEnclosureFanAusEnclosureDeviceIndex.name: ausEnclosureFanAusEnclosureDeviceIndex
ausEnclosureFanAusEnclosureDeviceIndex.description: The index of the ausEnclosureDeviceTable entry housing this fan.

ausEnclosureFanOrdinal.name: ausEnclosureFanOrdinal
ausEnclosureFanOrdinal.description: Zero-relative fan number within an enclosure.

ausEnclosureFanSpeed.name: ausEnclosureFanSpeed
ausEnclosureFanSpeed.description: Rotational speed of this fan in RPM.

ausEnclosurePowerSupplyTable.name: ausEnclosurePowerSupplyTable
ausEnclosurePowerSupplyTable.description: A list of enclosure power supplies.

ausEnclosurePowerSupplyIndex.name: ausEnclosurePowerSupplyIndex
ausEnclosurePowerSupplyIndex.description: A unique index value for each power supply.

ausEnclosurePowerSupplyAusEnclosureDevic.name: ausEnclosurePowerSupplyAusEnclosureDeviceIndex
ausEnclosurePowerSupplyAusEnclosureDevic.description: The index of the ausEnclosureDeviceTable entry housing this power supply.

ausEnclosurePowerSupplyOrdinal.name: ausEnclosurePowerSupplyOrdinal
ausEnclosurePowerSupplyOrdinal.description: Zero-relative power supply number within an enclosure.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorTable.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorTable
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorTable.description: A list of enclosure temperature sensors.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorIndex.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorIndex
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorIndex.description: A unique index value for each temperature sensor.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorAusEnclosur.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorAusEnclosureDeviceIndex
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorAusEnclosur.description: The index of the ausEnclosureDeviceTable entry housing this temperature sensor.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOrdinal.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOrdinal
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOrdinal.description: Zero-relative temperature sensor number within an enclosure.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOverTempera.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOverTemperature
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorOverTempera.description: Specifies whether this temperature sensor has detected an over temperature condition.

ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorDegrees.name: ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorDegrees
ausEnclosureTemperatureSensorDegrees.description: Temperature registered by this sensor in degrees Fahrenheit.

ausEnclosureSlotIndex.name: ausEnclosureSlotIndex
ausEnclosureSlotIndex.description: A unique index value for each slot.

ausEnclosureSlotAusEnclosureDeviceIndex.name: ausEnclosureSlotAusEnclosureDeviceIndex
ausEnclosureSlotAusEnclosureDeviceIndex.description: The index of the ausEnclosureDeviceTable entry housing this slot.

ausEnclosureSlotOrdinal.name: ausEnclosureSlotOrdinal
ausEnclosureSlotOrdinal.description: Zero-relative slot number within an enclosure.

ausEnclosureSlotPortId.name: ausEnclosureSlotPortId
ausEnclosureSlotPortId.description: Port ID number used by the device at this slot. Meaning is dependent on channel type. For example, SCSI channels would report device SCSI ID in this field. The field is a string to allow for a wide range of addressing schemes.

ausEnclosureSlotInsertions.name: ausEnclosureSlotInsertions
ausEnclosureSlotInsertions.description: Number of device insertions for this slot.

ausArrayIndex.name: ausArrayIndex
ausArrayIndex.description: A unique index value for each array beginning with 1.

ausArrayName.name: ausArrayName
ausArrayName.description: The name assigned to this array.

ausArrayCapacity.name: ausArrayCapacity
ausArrayCapacity.description: Capacity of this array in megabytes. This is data (usable) size, not the sum of all extents.

ausArrayType.name: ausArrayType
ausArrayType.description: RAID level used by this array.

ausArrayStripeSize.name: ausArrayStripeSize
ausArrayStripeSize.description: Stripe size used by this array.

ausArrayTaskCompletion.name: ausArrayTaskCompletion
ausArrayTaskCompletion.description: Percentage completion of running task, if any. Reports as 100 if no task is active.

ausArrayTaskPriority.name: ausArrayTaskPriority
ausArrayTaskPriority.description: Priority of the running task (if any).

ausArrayHostingControllerType.name: ausArrayHostingControllerType
ausArrayHostingControllerType.description: This field tells whether the hosting controller for this array is an actual physical controller, an aggregate controller (multiple controllers made to look like one through software), or an external RAID controller. This field is used to select the meaning of the following ausArrayControllerIndex field.

ausArrayHostingControllerIndex.name: ausArrayHostingControllerIndex
ausArrayHostingControllerIndex.description: This field associates this array with its hosting controller. if the ausArrayControllerType field equals physicalController, then this field is an index into the ausController table. If the ausArrayControllerType field equals aggregateController, then this field is an index into the ausAggregateController table. If the ausArrayControllerType field equal externalRaidController, then this field is an index into the ausExternalRaidDevice table.

ausArrayCacheStatus.name: ausArrayCacheStatus
ausArrayCacheStatus.description: Current write cache status of this array.

ausArrayMembership.name: ausArrayMembership
ausArrayMembership.description: For non-composite arrays (e.g., a straight mirror, RAID-1, set) this field is always 0. For composite arrays (e.g. stripe set of mirrors, RAID-10) this field indicates the position in the array hierarchy. If this is the topmost array in the hierarchy, this field will be 0. If this is a subordinate array in the hierarchy, this field is set to a value equal to the index of the entry in the Array Table locating its parent.

ausArrayID.name: ausArrayID
ausArrayID.description: The ID of this array on its hosting controller.

ausArrayPMStatus.name: ausArrayPMStatus
ausArrayPMStatus.description: Power Management Status for the Logical Drive.

ausStandByTimer.name: ausStandByTimer
ausStandByTimer.description: Period of inactivity, from 3 minutes to 3 hours, after which the drives spin rate is lowered. The default is zero.

ausPowerOffTimer.name: ausPowerOffTimer
ausPowerOffTimer.description: Period of inactivity, from 3 minutes to 3 hours, after which the disk drives are turned off. The default is zero.

ausVerifyTimer.name: ausVerifyTimer
ausVerifyTimer.description: Period of inactivity, from 1 hour to 24 hours. after which an inactive drive (a drive that is already powered down) is restarted and checked to verify its health. Once the check is completed, the drive is powered down and returns to its inactive state. The default is zero.

ausExtentIndex.name: ausExtentIndex
ausExtentIndex.description: A unique index value for each disk extent beginning with 1.

ausExtentAusDeviceIndex.name: ausExtentAusDeviceIndex
ausExtentAusDeviceIndex.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage device table that describes the physical disk containing this extent.

ausExtentSize.name: ausExtentSize
ausExtentSize.description: Size of this extent rounded to nearest megabyte.

ausExtentStartingLBALow.name: ausExtentStartingLBALow
ausExtentStartingLBALow.description: Starting disk LBA (logical buffer address) used by this extent (least significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausExtentStartingLBAHigh.name: ausExtentStartingLBAHigh
ausExtentStartingLBAHigh.description: Starting disk LBA (logical buffer address) used by this extent (most significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausExtentNumberOfBlocksLow.name: ausExtentNumberOfBlocksLow
ausExtentNumberOfBlocksLow.description: Number of disk blocks used by this extent (least significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausExtentNumberOfBlocksHigh.name: ausExtentNumberOfBlocksHigh
ausExtentNumberOfBlocksHigh.description: Number of disk blocks used by this extent (most significant 32 bits of 64 bit value).

ausExtentArrayMembership.name: ausExtentArrayMembership
ausExtentArrayMembership.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage array table selecting the array of which this extent is a member.

ausSpareIndex.name: ausSpareIndex
ausSpareIndex.description: A unique index value for each spare beginning with 1.

ausSpareAusDeviceIndex.name: ausSpareAusDeviceIndex
ausSpareAusDeviceIndex.description: Index into the Adaptec Universal Storage device table that describes the physical disk corresponding to this spare.

ausSpareType.name: ausSpareType
ausSpareType.description: Specifies whether this is a global spare (allocated to a controller), a dedicated spare (allocated to an array), an external RAID global spare (allocated to an external RAID controller), or a standby spare (allocated to a controller).

ausSpareAusControllerOrArrayIndex.name: ausSpareAusControllerOrArrayIndex
ausSpareAusControllerOrArrayIndex.description: If this is a global spare, this field contains an index into the Adaptec Universal Storage controller table selecting the controller for which the spare relationship exists. If this is a dedicated spare, this field contains an index into the Adaptec Universal Storage array table selecting the array for which the spare relationship exists. If this is an external RAID global spare, this field contains an index into the Adaptec Universal Storage external RAID device table selecting the controller for which the spare relationship exists.

ausEventLogNumEntries.name: ausEventLogNumEntries
ausEventLogNumEntries.description: The number of entries in the Event Log.

ausEventLogTable.name: ausEventLogTable
ausEventLogTable.description: A circular list of event log entries. The number of entries is given by the value of eventLogCount. Current maximum event log count is fixed at 256, but could be programmable (via MIB variable and/or .INI file) in the future.

ausEventLogTimeStamp.name: ausEventLogTimeStamp
ausEventLogTimeStamp.description: The time stamp assigned this event by middleware, in UNIX time_t format.

ausEventLogString.name: ausEventLogString
ausEventLogString.description: A text string containing the text of the event as generated by middleware.

ausEventType.name: ausEventType
ausEventType.description: A text string containing the type of the event as generated by middleware.

ausEvenCode.name: ausEvenCode
ausEvenCode.description: A value containing the code of the event as generated by middleware.

ausTrapObjectIndex.name: ausTrapObjectIndex
ausTrapObjectIndex.description: An index into a MIB table specifying the object associated with the trap. If the index is 0, then an index is not available (for example, for a deleted object).

ausTrapControllerType.name: ausTrapControllerType
ausTrapControllerType.description: Describes which type of controller generated this trap, and therefore which table is indexed.

ausTrapControllerStatus.name: ausTrapControllerStatus
ausTrapControllerStatus.description: Status of the controller that generated this trap.

ausTrapDeviceStatus.name: ausTrapDeviceStatus
ausTrapDeviceStatus.description: Status of the device that generated this trap.

ausTrapEnclosureStatus.name: ausTrapEnclosureStatus
ausTrapEnclosureStatus.description: Status of the enclosure that generated this trap.
